About 20 armed men invaded a secondary school in Kaduna State and kidnapped the Principal.
Report indicated that about 20 gunmen attacked the Government Technical Secondary School at Maraban Kajuru in Kajuru Local Government Area and kidnapped the Principal, Francis Maji, on Thursday.
It was indicated that the attack occurred one week after kidnappers invaded and kidnapped six female students of Engraver’s College at Kakau Daji in Chikun Local Government Area of the Kaduna State.
The wife of the Principal was said to have narrated that the kidnappers shot sporadically into the air to scare the students and teachers before they abducted the principal.







			
